
[1]herbaceous

   HERBA'CEOUS, a. [L. herbaceus.] Pertaining to herbs. Herbaceous plants
   are such as perish annually down to the root; soft, succulent
   vegetables. So, a herbaceous stem is one which is soft, not woody.
   Herbaceous, applied to animals by Derham, is not authorized. [See
   Herbivorous.]
